A Senior Advocate of Nigeria, SAN, Femi Falana, has called for the amendment of the Public Procurement Act to allow public universities to engage in bidding for contracts as a way of generating funds to keep them afloat. This is just as he called for a 10-year embargo on the setting up of new universities for the ones we have now to stabilise. Falana spoke at a commemorative symposium in honour of retired and dedicated persons organised by the Academic Staff Union of Universities, ASUU, the University of Lagos, UNILAG Chapter on Tuesday. Falana wondered why universities with a team of leading law teachers would still be hiring outsiders to handle their matters and why universities with great and good architecture department would give such jobs to contractors who are barely literate. Vanguard News Nigeria. HUMAN rights lawyer, Mr. Femi Falana, SAN, has challenged the Academic Staff Union of Universities, ASUU, to ensure the  unutilised  education intervention fund amounting to about N463 billion is immediately disbursed by the TETFUND to the tertiary institutions owned by the federal and state governments. May 9, 2018 In "Education" THE frontier of the anti corruption campaign of the Federal Government was expanded last week at a round-table organised by the Department of Jurisprudence and International Law of the University of Lagos, Akoka. April 7, 2016 In "Law & Human Rights" Lagos lawyer, Femi Falana, SAN, Prof Ralph Akinfeleye of University of Lagos, among other prominent personalities, yesterday, called for a democratic restructuring of the polity for the country to move forward. June 13, 2016 In "News"